<subSubSection pageId="100" pageNumber="858" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="100.[797,1391,3038,3465]" pageId="100" pageNumber="858">
Previously considered a race of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. Allen" authorityYear="1866" box="[1242,1382,3125,3150]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Rhogeessa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="100" pageNumber="858" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="parvula">R. parvula</taxonomicName>
, based on external and skull morphology; returned to species level based on bacular, external and skull morphology. Race cautiva resembles nominate in coloration, but is larger in measurements and body mass (where it resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. Allen" authorityYear="1866" box="[1080,1215,3357,3386]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Rhogeessa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="100" pageNumber="858" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tumida">R. tumida</taxonomicName>
); it has been speculated that it might be a separate species. Two subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
